            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "@justinmk \r\n\r\nwinver does not seem to be available on windows server 2022\r\n\r\n> winver : The term 'winver' is not recognized as the name of a cmdlet, function, script file, or operable program. Check the spelling of the name, or if a path was included, verify that the path is correct and try again.\r\n\r\n\r\nAlso `:help supported-platforms` does not help much if nvim does not start.\r\n\r\nWhile updating the documentation is better than the status quo, it would be more user-friendly if \r\n\r\n * neovim does not depend on `vcruntime140.dll` (static build? should be achievable with `/MT` flag)\r\n * neovim installer installs `vcruntime140.dll` (in the app folder, not globally)\r\n * neovim installer warns if `vcruntime140.dll` is missing\r\n\r\nThe first two options would be preferred in order to having nvim just working after installation.\r\n\r\nOtherwise the experience is pretty bad, as the executable seems to do nothing, while in reality the application does not start without any error message",
