            "body": "@bfredl \n\n> > Installation: setup\n\nI'm not sure who you are replying to here.\n\n> This does not say anything. Is this official binaries or from a package manager?\n\nWith \"For me, the official setup is the msi file/zip archive.\" I meant the setup and archive that can be downloaded from github, not what winget or scoop do on some platforms.\nI did only test the msi installer from here.\n\n> Our own binaries should only depend on UCRT, not any version of vcruntime.\n\nnvim depends on vcruntime140.dll, as shown in my third comment, I also tested the current release yesterday.\nMaybe not nvim directly, but one of its dependencies.\n\nInstalling  https://aka.ms/vs/17/release/vc_redist.x64.exe fixes the issue; nvim starts.\n\n",
